name: Bread pakoda
description: Bread pakoda or bread bajji are made with a spiced batter of gram flour aka besan, spices and salt with spicy, tangy potato stuffing.

name: Aloo pakora
description: Aloo pakora are soft melt-in-the-mouth fried potato fritters coated in a delicious, golden, crispy batter. It is also known as potato bajji

name: Onion Pakoda
description: Onion Pakoda is a deep fried Indian snack of crispy and tasty onion fritters made with gram flour (besan), spices and herbs.

name: Palak pakoda
description: Palak pakoda are delicious Indian spinach fritters made with fresh spinach leaves, gram flour, spices and herbs.

name: Gobhi pakoda
description: Cauliflower pakoda also known as gobi pakora are crunchy and delicious Indian fritters made with cauliflower florets, gram flour, spices and herbs.

name: Mirchi pakoda
description: Crisp mirch pakodas stuffed with a potato filling make for a great snack.

name: Kamal kakdi pakoda
description: Lotus stem fritters are very interesting way to incorporate it in our diet.

name: Paneer pakoda
description: Paneer pakora is a popular evening snack from North Indian cuisine. It is made by batter frying Indian cottage cheese aka paneer.

name: Soya chaap pakora
description: The cooked chaap are tossed in a tangy mixture made using onions, lime juice, green chilies, chaat masala, butter, and cooking cream.

name: Methi pakoda
description: Methi pakoda are spiced fried fritters made with gram flour batter, fresh fenugreek leaves, herbs and spices.

name: Ghiyaa pakoda
description: A spicy green masala paste involving cilantro, green chilies, cumin seeds and garlic is added to the besan batter which makes these bottle gourd fritters zesty.

name: Special paneer bread pakoda
description: Bread paneer pakora aka paneer bread bajji one of the popular indian street food recipe made with sandwich bread and paneer, aloo stuffing.

name: Spring roll
description: Spring roll is a traditional Chinese savory snack where a pastry sheet is filled with vegetables, rolled & fried.

name: French fries
description: French fries, are snack made from deep-fried thin strips potatoes. Fries are often salted and served with ketchup, mayonnaise, or vinegar.

name: Mix pakode
description: Mixed Vegetable pakora are veggie fritters made in South India. They are addictive, aromatic, crunchy and a delicious snack.

name: Soft Drinks
description: Life is better with a cold drink. Better quenched than sorry. Sip, sip, hooray.
